    Types of Operators in Java

Java operators are mainly divided into 8 categories:

1. Arithmetic Operators
Addition(+), Substraction(-), Multiplication(*), Division(/), Modulus(%)-remainder

2. Assignment Operators
(+=) add and assign, (-=) subtract and assign, (*=) multiply and assign, (/=) divide and assign, (%=) modulus and assign
--> Assignment operators work from right to left
example - All variables will store 5
int a, b, c;
a = b = c = 5;

3. Relational (Comparison) Operators
--> Relational operators in Java are used to compare two values.
--> They always return a boolean result (true or false)
(==), (!=), (>), (<), (>=), (<=)


